 the first hotkeyed item in your inventory slots.  I have other items that i keep in my inventory slots and wouldn't want to make a mistake during a life or death situation.<P>Does this also work with pumice stones?<P>------------------<BR>"First you cleave the knee, then you cleave the head."<P>Meyer Anklebane,<BR>on taking down Hill Giants<BR>45 Halfling Warrior, Xegony<P>"I am NOT a smurf!  There are no smurfs in Everquest!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Genjuro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Uh I don't get it, how is this any different than just rightclicking the hotkey'd jbewts?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Andervin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">This would be nice, so I wouldn't have to switch hotkey banks to use it.  But, if it requires you put it in the first bank, I also fail to see the usefullness. Besides, I've been playing 47 levels with that hotkey designated as a DD spell hotkey, would be hard to change now.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Blackacid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I obviously didn't do a good job explaining.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>The jboots need to go into the 3rd hotkey menu, in the 3rd slot. Not the 1st. This is helpful, so you don't have to switch hotkey menu's to activate the item your using, at least for me.<P>I'll take screen shots of what to do, and post them up this weekend, to better describe what I'm talking about.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR><B>Tezrian Vrix of Quellious</B><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">engine</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">This seems like a cool thing to try out.<P>thanks for the info guys!<P><BR>Redain Rainblade<BR>Level 23 Treehugger  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/biggrin.gif"><BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Andervin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hmm, I put the jboots in the 3rd slot of the 3rd hotkey bank, it didn't work for me.  Maybe I'm still doing it wrong.  Oh well.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Blackacid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I took screen shots of the whole process this weekend, I'll take some time out, and put together a better tutorial.<P>BTW: I stuck a Enduring Breathe potion in that slot, and it worked. So, I'm going to assume this will work with any charged item.<P><P>------------------<BR><B>Tezrian Vrix of Quellious</B><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Keryath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">works with any charged item, but the trick is it only works if you put it in the 3rd bank, 3rd slot, *THEN* switch back to the 1st bank.<P>If you have anything but the 1st bank up, it won't work.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Blackacid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">You are correct, and I suppose I should have made that more clear. I made a point of placing a pumice in the that slot just before I entered a dungeon - was glad I did, it worked out quite well on a few mobs.<P><P>------------------<BR><B>Tezrian Vrix of Quellious</B><P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
